                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12758593" author="karlpauls" created="Wed, 23 Sep 2009 06:04:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Our implicit bootdelegation detection assumes that if we walk a classloader.getClass.getClassloader() chain we will ultimately arrive at the bootclassloader which is represented by null. Apparently this is not true on android but at one point we get the same classloader for the next as the one we already have (i.e., we run into an endless loop). I commited a fix which makes sure we stop if we hit null or the same classloader again which seems to fix the issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
